SIMPLE: ruling
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruling
<hw>Rul"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Predominant; chief;
reigning; controlling; <as>as, a <ex>ruling</ex> passion; a
<ex>ruling</ex> sovereign</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Used in marking or engraving lines; <as>as, a
<ex>ruling</ex> machine or pen</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Predominant; chief; controlling; directing;
guiding; governing; prevailing; prevalent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ruling
<hw>Rul"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
rules; ruled lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A decision or rule of a judge or a
court, especially an oral decision, as in excluding evidence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rulingly</ent>⟦br⟧
